Package io.shiromi.saml.types

Class AbstractType<T>

java.lang.Object
io.shiromi.saml.types.AbstractType<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of object this class carries as values
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
BooleanType, GenericType, NullType, NumberType, StringType
abstract class AbstractType<T> extends Object implements Serializable
Instances of the class AbstractType represent a type value assignable to a YamlElement's value, each separate type has its own methods and implementation, however they can all be cast to GenericType as it has parameter <T> set to Object, therefore each subtype of this class can be cast to it.

Subtypes of this class behave a lot like their Java counterparts, e.g. StringType behaves similar to String, this class itself only exists for generalization and unification of types throughout, as well as basic methods implemented by each subclass.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Shiromi
